# Never-claims for {slug}
# Format: 1 forbidden claim per line. Comments start with #.
# Quality Gate #7 (factual claims check) will REJECT_IMMEDIATE any post containing these.
# No retry. The slot stays in 'manual_review_needed' with note "matched never-claim".

# === DEFAULT v1.4.0 — Source-Truth Hardening ===
# These default entries protect against the most common fabrications observed in v1.2.0/v1.3.0.

# Structural fabrications (chapters/modules/features the product doesn't actually have)
Any chapter title or section name not literally present in product-content.md.
Any module name in a course/syllabus not present in product-content.md STRUCTURE entries.
Any feature/capability of a SaaS not present in product-content.md.
Any reference to "chapter N" / "module Y" / "section X" with a number that doesn't exist in the product structure.

# Anecdote fabrications (stories adjacent to the product, not from the product)
Any persona/case-study/customer-story not present in product-content.md EXAMPLES entries (unless explicitly attributed: "FN m'a raconté que...").
Any specific named person/company appearing as an example in promotion that isn't documented in the product itself.
Any sensory detail (specific date, location, weather, time of day) describing an author's process scene without source.

# Process inventions (v1.3.0 anti-pattern — see anti-fabrication-contract.md Lenny example)
The author tried writing/building the product without AI for any duration before using AI (unless ledger confirms a pre-AI phase).
The author had previous human-only manuscripts or drafts.
The author tested N different tools/approaches before settling (unless ledger confirms specific N).

